      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of model predictions to experimental measurements with uncertainty characterization; mean relative error < 15% across all validation points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values compared against experimental measurements at five operating points. Mean relative error is 8.3%; however, uncertainty quantification of experimental measurements relies on a single replicate per condition rather than the three replicates required at Gradation 2. The spread across operating points shows one outlier at 3 L/min / 3000 RPM with 14.9% relative error, and propagated experimental uncertainty bands were estimated post-hoc from literature coefficients of variation rather than measured directly in this study. The output comparison therefore satisfies the directional accuracy criterion but does not fully meet the uncertainty characterization requirement for Gradation 2."
    },
